            "type": "text",
            "text": "Integrating Chatterbox into Your API Stack"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "To integrate Chatterbox, use its RESTful API endpoints with authentication via API keys. Implement retry logic for rate limits and monitor latency with tools like Prometheus. Ensure error handling covers common HTTP status codes such as 429 (Too Many Requests) and 503 (Service Unavailable)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cost Management and Optimization"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Optimize costs by caching frequent responses, batching requests where possible, and setting usage alerts. Analyze API logs to identify inefficient patterns, such as redundant calls or oversized payloads. Consider using Chatterbox's async endpoints for non-real-time tasks to reduce peak load expenses."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Advanced Use Cases and Scaling"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For high-throughput scenarios, leverage load balancing across multiple API keys and implement circuit breakers to maintain reliability. Test scaling with synthetic traffic to validate performance under load, and document failover procedures to minimize downtime during outages."
          }
        ]
